The paper discusses a learning framework for Inductive Logic Programming (ILP) under the answer set semantics, which involves common-sense knowledge and exceptions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the ILASP3 system on synthetic and real datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories.
